      "content": "Build commands: pnpm dev (Turbopack), pnpm build. TypeScript incremental type-check with 60s timeout via hooks. Test commands: test:api, test:code, test:all"
    },
    {
      "timestamp": 1782499005965,
      "source": "manual",
      "category": "testing",
      "content": "Playwright generation test (2026-06-26): sandbox creation failed with default 1440 min timeout on Hobby Vercel plan; set SANDBOX_TIMEOUT_MINUTES=45 in .env.local to enable creation. Chat-based generation produced 7 files (index.css, App.jsx, Header.jsx, Hero.jsx, Features.jsx, MenuPreview.jsx, Footer.jsx), but preview sandbox crashed because the generated code imported 'Facebook' from lucide-react, which is not a valid export. Download ZIP reported 'No files to download yet' because sandboxFiles state was empty after apply; /api/get-sandbox-files returned 'No active sandbox'. After refresh, the generated code/Code tab was empty because generationProgress state (files/streamedCode) and conversationContext.lastGeneratedCode are not persisted to localStorage/DB; the page also auto-restarted a new generation from leftover sessionStorage targetUrl=example.com."
    },
    {
      "timestamp": 1782512784887,
      "source": "manual",
      "category": "testing",
      "content": "Verification results (2026-06-26) after implementing generation persistence + lucide sanitization: (1) pnpm tsc --noEmit passed clean; (2) pnpm build passed. Playwright run: generated a bakery landing page, file explorer showed 5 files (index.css, App.tsx, Header.tsx, Hero.tsx, Features.tsx, Footer.tsx). Download ZIP succeeded and produced a 5.0KB archive with src/main.jsx, App.jsx, App.tsx, index.css, Header.tsx, Hero.tsx, package.json, vite.config.js, tailwind.config.js, postcss.config.js. Refresh test: chat messages persisted but the Code tab file explorer did NOT re-appear; the page switched back to View tab and showed only the empty \"Sandbox Ready\" state. The restored files were written to a fresh sandbox (POST /api/restore-files 200) but the generationProgress.files state was not restored from localStorage/DB on refresh. Root cause: the mount restore only sets files if savedSession.fileCache exists, but the URL was restored from the old session with a different sandbox ID, or the fileCache was stored as sandboxFiles and the conversion path fails when fileCache is an empty object."
    }
  ],
